A retired director of Health with Safana local government in Katsina state, Salisu Runka has been released by his abductors 24 hours after his family paid N1.5 million ransom. Daily Trust gathered from close family associates that upon his release, Runka was rushed to Dutsinma General Hospital for medical attention. Runka was abducted while working on his farm along Runka- Gora junction in the presence of some of his children who later rushed to town to inform their mother, Malam Ummah Kanti who later reported the matter to police. The spokesman of the state police command SP Gambo Isah while confirming the incidence however said the command wasn't aware of any ransom payment as the family did not disclosed. He said the victim was picked up by the police while wandering in the forest and rushed to hospital.